{
  "texts": [
    "In addition to the widely used homogeneous graph pooling techniques, a series of innovative pooling methods have emerged for complex networks such as heterogeneous graphs and hypergraphs.",
    "These methods not only enrich the toolbox of graph neural networks but also significantly improve the performance of the models when dealing with complex data structures.",
    "Semantic-aware Attentive Pooling (SAAP) (Yang et al. 2023) is a pooling strategy based on Relational-GCN (Schlichtkrull et al. 2018), designed for heterogeneous graph classification tasks.",
    "This pooling method computes attention scores between nodes using both semantic and structural information.",
    "HG-Pool (Wu et al. 2021a) is a heterogeneous graph pooling method that employs specific pooled graph neural networks for different types of nodes."
  ]
}